div.div:
FIX: beamsClient code in app.blade.php
Additional functions have been added to the beamsClient code in app.blade.php. The new code registers the device with Beams, logs the device ID, adds a "dashboard" interest to the device, retrieves the current interests of the device and handles any errors that occur during these processes. This improves interaction logging and error handling for Pusher Push Notifications.

Remove Pusher Push Notifications code from service-worker.js
The Pusher Push Notifications code has been removed from the service-worker.js file. Previously, this code initialized the Beams client and handled received notifications. This removal makes the service-worker.js file only import the necessary scripts, improving modularity and separation of concerns.

Implement Pusher Push Notifications on app.blade.php
Pusher Push Notifications have been integrated directly into the app.blade.php file with additional updates to the service-worker.js for optimized handling of notifications. The added script in app.blade.php initializes the Beams client using a specific instance id, enabling the start of the notifications client, while the updates to service-worker.js modify the process of handling received notifications for improved application functionality.

Move service-worker.js to public directory
The service-worker.js is moved to the public directory in the src folder as part of the refactoring process for Beams integration. Relocating the file improves the organization of the project structure and better accommodates the simplified PusherPushNotifications.Client implementation and the new streamlined process for displaying web push notifications.

Refactor service-worker.js for Beams integration
The update simplifies the service-worker.js file to specifically focus on Beams integration. It removes the previous multi-state registration process and direct BeamClient usage, and introduces a more streamlined approach with an instance of PusherPushNotifications.Client. On notification received, a web push notification is now immediately displayed.
